#: ../../E/epsilon.rst:5
msgid "epsilon"
msgstr "epsilon"

#: ../../E/epsilon.rst:7
msgid "[see :ref:`delta`\\]"
msgstr "[\\ :ref:`delta`\\ を参照]"

#: ../../E/epsilon.rst:9
msgid "n\\. A small quantity of anything. \"The cost is epsilon.\""
msgstr "名詞。何かのごく少量。「The cost is epsilon(費用はepsilonだ)。」"

#: ../../E/epsilon.rst:13
msgid ""
"adj. Very small, negligible; less than :ref:`marginal`\\. \"We can get this "
"feature for epsilon cost.\""
msgstr ""
"形容詞。非常に小さい、無視できる。\\ :ref:`marginal`\\ 未満。「We can get this feature for "
"epsilon cost(この機能はepsilonの費用で手に入る)。」"

#: ../../E/epsilon.rst:17
msgid ""
"within epsilon of: close enough to be indistinguishable for all practical "
"purposes, even closer than being within delta of. \"That's not what I asked "
"for, but it's within epsilon of what I wanted.\" Alternatively, it may mean "
"not close enough, but very little is required to get it there: \"My program "
"is within epsilon of working.\""
msgstr ""
"within epsilon of:実用上あらゆる目的において区別がつかないほど十分に近い、within delta "
"ofであるよりもさらに近い。「That's not what I asked for, but it's within epsilon of what "
"I wanted(求めていたものとは違うが、欲しかったもののwithin epsilon "
"ofだ)。」あるいは、十分に近くはないが、そこに到達するのにごくわずかしか必要としない、という意味のこともある。「My program is "
"within epsilon of working(私のプログラムは動作するwithin epsilon ofだ)。」"
